            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Henry Borneman collected these 24 letters, typescripts, and clippings relating to Brook Farm and Fourierism. Many of the letters are to John S. Dwight. Also included is &quot;Reminiscences of Brook Farm and its Founder: A Lecture Read at Waltham, Monday, March 26, 1900,&quot; written by Frank B. Sanborn of Concord, Mass., and published in <emph render="italic">American Transcendental Quarterly</emph>, 26 (Spring 1975).</p>
                                 <p>The items in this collection were microfilmed in 1942 for Arthur E. Bestor, Jr., who gave them to the Survey in 1951.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


